{{!
    @template mod_customcert/email_certificate_html

    The certificate verification result

    Classes required for JS:
    * None

    Data attibutes required for JS:
    * All data attributes are required

    Context variables required for this template:
    * isstudent Are we sending to a student?
    * isteacher Are we sending to a teacher?
    * isother Are we sending to an email address specified in the certificate settings?
    * userfullname The name of the user who owns the certificate.
    * coursefullname The name of the course.
    * certificatename The name of the certificate.

    Example context (json):
    {
        "isstudent": "true",
        "isteacher": "false",
        "isother": "false,
        "userfullname": "Angus MacGyver",
        "coursefullname": "Survival as an '80s action hero",
        "certificatename": "Making a nuclear weapon from a packet of rubber bands"
    }
}}
{$a->student} has received their certificate: '<i>{$a->certificate}</i>'
for {$a->course}.

You can review it here:

<a href="{$a->url}">Certificate Report</a>.